GET /v1/transactions/{businessTransactionId}/receipt

GET /v1/transactions/{businessTransactionId}/executions/{executionId}/receipt

Locked architectural decisions
One Receipt is issued for each terminal Execution (COMPLETED or FAILED).
The Receipt is derived from the Execution Trust Record and never replaces it.
executionStatus uses the final execution lifecycle state, consistent with the Execution Lifecycle Model.
The Receipt contains the cryptographic hash and signature required for independent verification, making it the portable trust artifact defined in the Receipt Model.


